"props":357,"children":358},{},[359,361,367],{"type":27,"value":360},"Congratulations! TailwindCSS should now be usable within your ",{"type":19,"tag":102,"props":362,"children":364},{"className":363},[],[365],{"type":27,"value":366},".md",{"type":27,"value":368}," files.",{"type":19,"tag":370,"props":371,"children":373},"h3",{"id":372},"example",[374],{"type":27,"value":375},"Example:",{"type":19,"tag":49,"props":377,"children":378},{},[379],{"type":27,"value":380},"Here is an example of this article using TailwindCSS alongside Vitepress' built in markdown formatting:",{"type":19,"tag":111,"props":382,"children":387},{"className":383,"code":385,"language":386,"meta":6},[384],"language-md","# Configuring TailwindCSS to work with Vitepress\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col items-center mt-10 sm:flex-row\">\n  \u003Cimg src=\"../images/vite-logo.svg\" alt=\"Vite package logo\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 12px;\" />\n  \u003Cp class=\"italic text-gray-500\">\n    I've found myself feeling limited by the styles provided by the framework so I looked into what it takes to use a stylesheet.\n  \u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\nA bit of searching around ended up pointing me towards [this Github issue](https://github.com/vuejs/vitepress/issues/62) which helps a user integrate [Tailwindcss](https://tailwindcss.com/), a framework I've been using professionally and in personal projects for awhile now.\n\nAccording to the responses within the issue, there are two ways of bringing in TailwindCSS:\n\n**1. Import TailwindCSS through their CDN:**\n","md",[388],{"type":19,"tag":102,"props":389,"children":390},{"__ignoreMap":6},[391],{"type":27,"value":385},{"title":6,"searchDepth":393,"depth":393,"links":394},2,[395],{"id":372,"depth":396,"text":375},3,"markdown","content:tailwindcss-with-vitepress.md","content","tailwindcss-with-vitepress.md","tailwindcss-with-vitepress",1731129366147]